HEADWORD: Monophysite
<hw>Mo*noph"y*site</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>mo`nos</grk> single + <?/ nature: cf. F.
<ets>monophysite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a
sect, in the ancient church, who maintained that the human and divine in
Jesus Christ constituted but one composite nature. Also used
adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

